channel.title: [317] Can't go underground?
channel.description:
Hmm. I'm wondering, is it imposible to go underground? I'm trying to go into the Varrock sewers, using this code: [code] if (objectID == 881) { triggerTele(3237,3458,-1); //triggerTele(X,Y, height); } [/code]
However. This teleports me up. By 2 levels. I tried other height levels, but always with the same results. Either I stay on the ground, go up 1 level, or go up 2 levels. But I can't seem to go underground. Hence why I ask, is it impossible to go underground?
PS: Inb4 use heightLevel, it has the same results, and so does setting the height manually in my savefile
Regards, SirPali

item.title: [317] Can't go underground?
item.dc:creator: @SirPali SirPali
item.description:

Mental Piracy:

to go “underground” you must add 6400 to the y coords so say you were ate 2500x 3000y, underground of that exact location would be 2500x 9400y

Well isn’t that something, it works
Thanks for your help
